<h4 id="1--tex-and-latex">1  Tex and Latex</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Tex is about formatting</li>
  <li>Latex is about content</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="compiling">Compiling</h4>
<p>Most latex compilers need to be re-run several times in order to get a camera ready copy.</p>
<ol>
  <li>if there was a .idx file, remember its content</li>
  <li>run latex</li>
  <li>if the .idx file changed due to latex compiler, then run <strong>makeindex</strong> to redo the <strong>.ind</strong> file.</li>
  <li>if the .aux file generated by the latex contains a \bibdata line, then it means we are using a
<strong>.bib</strong> file, Therefore, run <strong>bibtex</strong></li>
  <li>if the .bbl file changes because of this, then remember to rerun latex.</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="2-cls-and-sty">2. cls and sty</h4>
<ol>
  <li>.cls files are loaded with <strong>\documentclass{}</strong> command, .cls files are called classes.
    <ul>
      <li>a class file will complete define the strucutre of a document</li>
      <li>they are mandatory</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>.sty files are loaded with <strong>\usepackage{}</strong> command, .sty files are called style files, or just
packages.
    <ul>
      <li>package or style file, they are provide something that class files doesnâ€™t accommodate, amendment
to class files, or improvement.</li>
      <li>they are optional</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

<h4 id="3-bst-file">3. .bst file</h4>
<p>.bst file is used to specify the bibliography style</p>

